Thanks for joining our live coverage on an extraordinary day in court, with adult-film star Stormy Daniels taking the stand.

It was a tense courtroom, with Daniels warned to dial back her comments at times. Prosecutors were also told to limit their questions regarding the salacious details of her alleged sexual encounter with Trump (which Trump has denied ever took place).

Here's our full wrap of what happened in court today.

This page was edited by Tiffany Wertheimer, Lisa Lambert, Brandon Livesay and Phil McCausland. The writers were Sam Hancock and Sean Seddon, and we had Madeline Halpert and Kayla Epstein in court.

Court doesn't sit on Wednesday, so we'll be back on Thursday, when Stormy Daniels will once again take to the stand to continue her testimony.

The main character, named John, was feeling anxious as he waited for his job interview. He had prepared for this moment for weeks, but he still couldn't shake off the nervousness. He took a deep breath and tried to calm himself down.

Suddenly, the door opened, and a woman walked in. "Hello, John. I'm glad you made it on time. Please, come in." John followed her into the room and took a seat across from her. "Thank you for coming in today. I'm your interviewer, and I'll be asking you some questions about your qualifications and experience."

John cleared his throat and tried to sound confident. "Of course, I'm happy to answer any questions you may have." The interviewer smiled and leaned forward. "Let's start with your educational background. Where did you go to school, and what did you study?"

John explained that he had a Bachelor's degree in Business Administration from a prestigious university. He had also taken additional courses to improve his skills in areas like marketing and finance. The interviewer nodded and asked him about his work experience. John told her about his previous jobs and how he had gained valuable experience in each one.

As the interview went on, John became more and more relaxed. He answered each question with confidence, and the interviewer seemed impressed. "I think you're a great fit for this position," she said at the end of the interview. "I'll be in touch soon with my decision."

John thanked her for her time and left the room feeling hopeful. He knew he had done his best, and now it was just a matter of waiting. He couldn't help but wonder if he would get the job or not, but he tried to stay positive. He had worked hard for this, and he deserved to be successful.
